From 93a47101d35f40d0a58d8662cbae1f415ae470de Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 22:23:53 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 15/17] task4: final publish rename shares the archive rollback
 path

A failure on the consolidated-note publish os.replace now rolls the
just-archived members back, unlinks the temp note and records a failed
cache entry, exactly like a mid-archive failure; previously it only hit
the per-group catch-all (logged, no cache record, members stranded in
the archive). Reviewer-prescribed fast-follow with regression test.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 coral/hub/consolidation.py            | 65 ++++++++++++++++-----------
 tests/test_gate_consolidation_core.py | 61 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 99 insertions(+), 27 deletions(-)

diff --git a/coral/hub/consolidation.py b/coral/hub/consolidation.py
