        original member is atomically moved (``os.replace``, never copied)
        into ``<public_root>/note_archive/<group_id>/`` first; only once
        every member has been archived does the temp note become
-       ``consolidated-<group_id>.md`` in ``shared_notes_dir``. If any member
-       fails to archive (vanished mid-pass, cross-device dir, a locked
-       file, ...), archiving stops immediately, everything already archived
-       THIS group is moved back into ``shared_notes_dir`` on a best-effort
-       basis (each move attempted in its own try/except -- a rollback
-       failure is logged, never raised), the temp note is deleted, and the
-       group is recorded as failed. A group therefore never ends up
-       half-archived with its consolidated note already published, and
-       never gets published while a member is still missing.
+       ``consolidated-<group_id>.md`` in ``shared_notes_dir``. BOTH the
+       archive loop and the final publish ``os.replace`` share the same
+       rollback treatment: if either fails (a member vanished mid-pass, a
+       cross-device dir, a locked file, the rename to the final name itself
+       failing, ...), everything already archived THIS group is moved back
+       into ``shared_notes_dir`` on a best-effort basis (each move attempted
+       in its own try/except -- a rollback failure is logged, never
+       raised), the temp note is deleted, and the group is recorded as
+       failed. A group therefore never ends up half-archived with its
+       consolidated note already published, and never gets published while
+       a member is still missing.
     8. Failures record ``status: "failed"`` in the cache (still logged via
        the module logger) so a broken group isn't retried every pass either
        -- but member notes and the group itself are left completely
